com.microfocus.adm.pulse.pluginapi.chain

Interface PulseMeasurementBuilder


  • public interface PulseMeasurementBuilder

    Builder used to create measurements of previously registered metrics. Only measurements constructed with this builder are accepted by the Pulse framework. The builder can be used to create multiple measurements by varying the properties between each call to build(), with each property being persisted between each call.

    Only a single value can be held by the builder at any one time. Calling a value setter will reset the value to that type automatically such that if one metric is a string value and the next is a double value, calling doubleValue(double) would drop the string value.

    The builder doesn't perform validation on the values provided until a measurement is built with a call to build() at which time the current value contained in the builder

    Each property setter returns this builder allowing property calls to be chained together, e.g. builder.metric(linesOfCode).integerValue(32768.build()

    Since:
    19.1.1

    • Method Detail

      • build

        PulseMeasurement build()

        Build the measurement. If the values provided to the builder would result in an invalid measurement this method will throw an IllegalStateException exception, for example if you provide an invalid double value to a numeric type.

        Enforced limitations are;

        • A value must be provided.
        • The metric definition this is a measurement for must be provided and come from PulseMetricRegistrar.
        • Numeric values can not be Double.NaN, Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY or Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY
        • String values can be empty but not null.
        Returns:
        New PulseMeasurement ready for recording via PulseMeasurementReporter. Can not be null.
        Since:
        19.1.1

      • path

        PulseMeasurementBuilder path(String path)
